@marcospereira added example to clarify my case
@wsargent exactly, I have to create my own modified `AhcWSComponents` so I can access the `StandaloneWSClient` built in there. It would be simpler if the `AhcWSComponents` would also expose a `StandaloneWSClient` next to the play `WsClient`.

My current workaround:
```scala
trait AhcWSWithStandaloneComponents {

  def environment: Environment
  def configuration: Configuration
  def applicationLifecycle: ApplicationLifecycle
  def materializer: Materializer
  def executionContext: ExecutionContext

  private lazy val standaloneAhcWSClient = {
    implicit val mat = materializer
    implicit val ec = executionContext
    val asyncHttpClient = new AsyncHttpClientProvider(environment, configuration, applicationLifecycle).get
    new StandaloneAhcWSClient(asyncHttpClient)
  }

  lazy val standaloneWsClient: StandaloneWSClient = standaloneAhcWSClient

  lazy val wsClient: WSClient = {
    new AhcWSClient(standaloneAhcWSClient)
  }
}
```

Anyway, this is more a suggestion, nice to have but not blocking.
